+### Link Quality & Error States
+
+Each ARC cover entity now includes two extra attributes:
+
+- `rf_strength`: Radio link quality derived from the `Rxx` field (0–100 %).  
+  - 80–100 % → Excellent  
+  - 60–79 % → Good  
+  - 40–59 % → Fair  
+  - Below 40 % → Weak / unreliable
+
+- `error_state`: One of `"OK"`, `"Not Listening"`, or `"Not Paired"`, depending on ARC reply codes (`Enl`, `Enp`).
+
+Example attributes visible in Home Assistant:
+
+```yaml
+current_position: 0.45
+current_tilt_position: 0.50
+rf_strength: 72.9
+error_state: OK
+```
+
+When a motor is out of range or unpaired:
+
+```yaml
+rf_strength: 0.0
+error_state: Not Listening
+```
+
